What is docker  and what is key feature?

Ans.: Docker is container management tool' used for deployment purpose. It is a software container 		 platform. There is no pre-allocation of RAM in docker like VM.

         Docker containers are light in weight, cheaper, can create number of containers from single 		 image. It uses only Host OS. Over which we create container engine by

         using Docker and can install various applications by sing docker images.

How docker help on manage multiple environment and multiple version same software ?

Ans.: We can run particular image in multiple environment. Docker server recieve the command the 		 commands from the docker client through CLI or Rest API. Docker

         client and server can be present on the same host (machine) or diff host.Host OS---->cintainer 	 engine---->apps or Host OS----> VM -----> container engine ----> apps



